To compute the average dependency distance for the given Swedish sentence, we first need to identify the words and their dependencies:

1. Men (conjunction) - depends on the main sentence
2. jag (subject) - depends on tog (1 distance)
3. tog (verb) - head of the clause
4. bara (adverb) - modifies tog (1 distance)
5. jätte (intensifier) - modifies lite (1 distance)
6. lite (adjective) - modifies information (1 distance)
7. information (object) - depends on tog (1 distance)
8. från (preposition) - modifies information (2 distance)
9. Wikipedia (noun) - depends on från (1 distance)
10. eftersom (subordinating conjunction) - introduces the dependent clause (1 distance)
11. jag (subject) - depends on hade (1 distance)
12. redan (adverb) - modifies hade (1 distance)
13. hade (verb) - head of this clause
14. tillräckligt (adverb) - modifies med (1 distance)
15. med (preposition) - modifies information (2 distance)
16. information (object) - depends on hade (2 distance)
17. från (preposition) - modifies information (2 distance)
18. mina (possessive determiner) - modifies källor (1 distance)
19. andra (adjective) - modifies källor (1 distance)
20. källor (noun) - depends on hade (3 distance)

Calculating the distances:
- Men: 0 (does not depend on any specific token)
- I to tog: 1
- Bara to tog: 1
- Jätte to lite: 1
- Lite to information: 1
- Information to tog: 1
- Från to information: 2
- Wikipedia to från: 1
- Eftersom: 1 (does not depend on specific token for distance)
- Jag to hade: 1
- Redan to hade: 1
- Hade: 0 (does not depend on another token)
- Tillräckligt to med: 1
- Med to information: 2
- Information to hade: 2
- Från to information: 2
- Mina to källor: 1
- Andra to källor: 1
- Källor to hade: 3

Now, summing these distances: 
1 + 1 + 1 + 1 + 1 + 1 + 2 + 1 + 1 + 1 + 1 + 1 + 1 + 2 + 2 + 2 + 1 + 1 + 3 = 19

The number of words/tokens in the sentence, including punctuation, is 20.

Therefore, the average dependency distance is calculated as follows:

Average Dependency Distance = Total Distance / Total Tokens 
= 19 / 20 
